{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"f3c671e3622493f0843abb26049f341e008a022f777957a5531f697447a0400f","slug":"papers.rram-devices.index","location":"/papers/rram-devices/index.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"RRAM Devices","description":"Resistive RAM, oxide switching, filament formation, sneak currents, crossbar arrays, and in-memory computing.","content_includes_title":false,"exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"index.md","url":"/index-7a0401a29aeb7306c58efc5a7838f40a.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What is this domain?","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"key":"mkTphjV5yy"}],"identifier":"what-is-this-domain","label":"What is this domain?","html_id":"what-is-this-domain","implicit":true,"key":"a3i9n2fsqQ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Resistive random-access memory (RRAM) is a class of non-volatile memory technology in which data is stored as the resistance state of a metal-insulator-metal stack. Switching between high-resistance (HRS) and low-resistance (LRS) states is achieved by the formation and dissolution of conductive filaments — typically composed of oxygen vacancies or metal cations — within a thin oxide layer. RRAM devices are among the most mature memristive technologies and have reached commercial production in several forms.","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"BnOGXgEYd5"}],"key":"Pz57sWOM3Z"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Why it matters","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"mHSG7zJSgx"}],"identifier":"why-it-matters","label":"Why it matters","html_id":"why-it-matters","implicit":true,"key":"TdcfC1LqJi"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"RRAM offers a compelling combination of properties for neuromorphic computing: nanoscale scalability, CMOS compatibility, analogue conductance tuning, low switching energy, and non-volatility. Dense crossbar arrays of RRAM devices can perform vector-matrix multiplication in the analogue domain at the location of weight storage, eliminating the von Neumann bottleneck and enabling in-memory computing at a fraction of the energy cost of digital approaches.","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"key":"uIU4RC3Nsd"}],"key":"V1zPIaMNxE"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Core concepts","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"nBtg6rjqdI"}],"identifier":"core-concepts","label":"Core concepts","html_id":"core-concepts","implicit":true,"key":"KSjAGbDTNx"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Filamentary switching mechanism","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"tFjIFWsHod"}],"key":"tPWmqbh3sd"},{"type":"text","value":" — set (LRS) and reset (HRS) transitions involve the formation and rupture of nanoscale conductive filaments driven by Joule heating, ion drift, and redox reactions","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"CSmCNQMGUG"}],"key":"ifqhutT07t"}],"key":"djush9KrVr"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Forming process","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"key":"FQjd2cUYGU"}],"key":"y01qNIHZcQ"},{"type":"text","value":" — the initial high-voltage electroforming step that creates the first conductive filament and establishes the switching regime; a source of device-to-device variability","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"key":"Z8VTzTSS1N"}],"key":"iG5eLgOPks"}],"key":"MtE2r4bcmp"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cycle-to-cycle and device-to-device variability","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"AG6YAETJgS"}],"key":"CFbUK6eJC0"},{"type":"text","value":" — stochastic filament dynamics lead to resistance distributions rather than fixed resistance values, a major challenge for reliable analogue weight storage","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"C6slmA9NNA"}],"key":"a8vlSISsmG"}],"key":"qthpmISE9I"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Sneak current paths","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"key":"wb8jBcsrgD"}],"key":"FllPz6Xw12"},{"type":"text","value":" — in passive crossbar arrays without selector devices, current